===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|schal|lang=enm}} (first and third person singular form of {{term|schulen|lang=enm}}), from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|sceal|lang=ang}} (first and third person singular of {{term|sculan||to be obligated or obliged to, shall, must, owe, ought to|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*skulaną}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*skel-||to owe, be under obligation}}. Cognate with Scots {{term|sall|lang=sco}}, {{term|sal||shall|lang=sco}}, Dutch {{term|zal|lang=nl}} {{gloss|"shall"; from {{term|zullen|lang=nl}}}}, German {{term|soll|lang=de}} {{gloss|"ought to"; from {{term|sollen|lang=de}}}}, Danish {{term|skal|lang=da}} {{gloss|"shall"; from {{term|skulle|lang=da}}}}. Related to {{l|en|shild}}.

